# Addison Daemon — Environment Configuration Example
#
# This file is a public-safe example. It is not live configuration.
#
# Copy this file to .env on the local machine and fill in real values.
# Keep .env private and untracked.

# --- Inference Provider ---
# OpenRouter API key for inference calls.
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# Optional: override the default max output tokens for inference requests.
# If unset, the daemon uses a code-level fallback (currently 4096).
# OPENROUTER_MAX_TOKENS=4096

# --- TTS Provider (Primary) ---
# ElevenLabs API key for daemon-backed voice synthesis.
# If unset or invalid, the daemon treats ElevenLabs as unavailable
# and falls through to the Kokoro fallback.
ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=

# --- TTS Provider (Fallback) ---
# Kokoro-FastAPI runs as a local Docker sidecar on port 8880.
# No API key is needed — Kokoro is reached via local HTTP.
# The daemon falls back to Kokoro when ElevenLabs is unavailable.
# If Kokoro is also unavailable, voice degrades truthfully to no-audio.
#
# To start Kokoro separately:
#   docker run --rm -p 8880:8880 ghcr.io/remsky/kokoro-fastapi-cpu:v0.2.4

# --- Notes ---
# Voice is optional and additive. The system is fully functional without
# any TTS provider configured.
#
# Do not commit .env files with real credentials to any repository.
